Let $$Det(P) = \left| {\matrix{
   {{a_2}} &amp; {{b_2}} &amp; {{c_3}}  \cr 
   {{a_3}} &amp; {{b_3}} &amp; {{c_3}}  \cr 

 } } \right|$$<br><br>$$ = {a_1}({b_2}{c_3} - {b_3}{c_2}) - {a_2}({b_1}{c_3} - {b_3}{c_1}) + {a_3}({b_1}{c_2} - {b_2}{c_1})$$<br><br>Now, maximum value of Det (P) = 6<br><br>If $${a_1} = 1$$, $${a_2} =  - 1$$, $${a_3} = 1$$, $${b_2}{c_3} = {b_1}{c_3} = {b_1}{c_2} = 1$$ and $${b_3}{c_2} = {b_3}{c_1} = {b_2}{c_1} =  - 1$$<br><br>But it is not possible as<br><br>$$({b_2}{c_3})({b_3}{c_1})({b_1}{c_2})$$ = $$-$$1<br><br>and $$({b_1}{c_3})({b_3}{c_2})({b_2}{c_1})$$ = 1<br><br>i.e., $${b_1}{c_2}{b_3}{c_1}{c_2}{c_3}$$ = 1 and $$-$$1<br><br>Similar contradiction occurs when<br><br>$${a_1} = 1$$, $${a_2} = 1$$, $${a_3} = 1$$, $${b_2}{c_1} = {b_3}{c_1} = {b_1}{c_2}$$ = 1 and $${b_3}{c_2} = {b_1}{c_3} = {b_1}{c_2} =  - 1$$<br><br>Now, for value to be 5 one of the terms must be zero but that will make 2 terms zero which means answer cannot be 5<br><br>Now, <br><br>$$\left| {\matrix{
   1 &amp; 1 &amp; 1  \cr 
   { - 1} &amp; 1 &amp; 1  \cr 
   1 &amp; { - 1} &amp; 1  \cr 

 } } \right| = 4$$<br><br>Hence, maximum value is 4

