 } } \right| = \alpha  - 2\beta  + \gamma  = 1$$ [from Eq. (iv)]<br/><br/>Equation of plane P is given by $$x - 2y + z = 1$$<br/><br/>Hence, perpendicular distance of the point (0, 1, 0) from the plane <br/><br/>$$P = {{\left| {0 - 2 \times 1 + 0 - 1} \right|} \over {\sqrt {{1^2} + {{( - 2)}^2} + {1^2}} }} = {{\left| 3 \right|} \over {\sqrt 6 }}$$<br/><br/>$$ \Rightarrow D = {\left( {{{\left| 3 \right|} \over {\sqrt 6 }}} \right)^2} = {9 \over 6} = 1.5$$

